The Federal Government has pleaded with host community in Ujevwu in Udu Local Government Area of Delta State, to cooperate with Julius Berger and other companies handling the ongoing railway project to ensure its completion by the May 2020 deadline. Minister of Transportation, Mr. Rotimi Amaechi, made the appeal during a visit to the Chairman of Udu Local Local Government Council, Hon Jite Brown, in his office at the weekend. According to the minister who was represented by Mr. Abdulrahmah Yusuf, several demands by the host community especially in the area of employment had been the reason the project had been delayed this long. He said the youths are demanding for more than 60 percent for community slot without which the project will be stopped completely. The Minister noted that employing them was not the issue but wondered how long it would take to train them to acquire the needed skills for the job at hand, especially for a project like the railway construction which requires professional skills. He stated that more than 40 percent of manual workers had already been employed by the contracting firm handling the project to create trust and friendship between it and host community, saying the project after completion would benefit Udu communities more. He said that when completed, it would be an easy access to transport goods from Ajaokuta steel to Premium Steel, Aladja and also create linkage to Warri Port and multiplier effect for improved socio-economic life of the people.